PO.Data: The flight authorization was acknowledged by this business partner
The flight was authorized by this business partner
Captain or PIC for the flight.
The Captain is the pilot in charge (PIC) and is typically the instructor on training flights.
The Contact/Phone number of a resonsible person for the flight.
The flight was aborted and the operations was not complted for some reason. See the comments.
Flight time where the fuel was purchased by the pilot.
Aircraft rentals are typically wet (fuel included) or dry (no fuel included). Dry rentals are similar to rental cars that have to be returned full at the end of the rental.
Is the flight course type one that should be charged a No-Show fee?
The Physical Inventory indicates a unique parameters for a physical inventory.
The student if the flight is an instructional flight.
The student is also usually the client ID for instructional flights.
The times for this flight were entered by this business partner.
For trips that will not land at the departure airport, this is the location of departure and represents the beginning of a "leg".
The destination airport where this flight "leg" terminates.
